        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Hardened malformed plugin/tool/schema metadata boundaries so hostile or unreadable synthetic plugin data is quarantined, omitted, diagnosed, or treated as absent instead of crashing provider routing, runtime tool resolution, Gateway/MCP catalogs, Codex prompt/report paths, plugin SDK helpers, bundle MCP catalog projection/materialization, and related assistant startup surfaces.\n- Kept fixtures synthetic: tests and notes use names like `fuzzplugin`, `mockplugin`, `mockplugin_status`, and `fuzz_move_*`, not the reported third-party plugin name.\n- Latest updates carry the already-validated plugin tool name into cached descriptor capture/execution, refresh main-drifted fixture types, gate Google/Vertex tool config after provider projection, and clean up the action-gate lint issue found by the changed gate.\n\n## Linked context\n\nWhich issue does this close?\n\nNo linked closing issue.\n\nWhich issues, PRs, or discussions are related?\n\nNo linked related issue.\n\nWas this requested by a maintainer or owner?\n\nMaintainer-directed hardening/debugging work.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: malformed runtime plugin tool schemas and hostile plugin/config/provider/manifest/native-approval/outbound-action/bundle-MCP metadata can crash, widen decisions, or bypass schema quarantine before normal OpenClaw diagnostics, setup, provider routing, gateway startup planning, Gateway catalog rendering, MCP loopback handling, approval forwarding, manifest/capability auth gating, provider payload conversion, prompt-cache setup, Codex reporting/instruction generation, plugin SDK normalization, agent-core tool lookup, cached plugin descriptor execution, static plugin tool registration, bundled capability runtime capture, bundle MCP catalog projection, or bundle MCP catalog materialization completes.\n\nReal environment tested: local focused Vitest through `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs`, local focused lint/format checks, branch-mode autoreview, synthetic/private-name scrub, and AWS Crabbox Linux `pnpm check:changed`. Blacksmith Testbox was unavailable in this shell because `blacksmith auth login` is required.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n- Force-pushed branch head `52e0654e9c38b2a5b798e853a2f30516b00ca706`.\n- AWS Crabbox changed gate on branch head `51e0789ad5`: `CRABBOX_AWS_REGION=us-east-1 CRABBOX_CAPACITY_REGIONS=us-east-1,us-east-2,us-west-2,eu-west-1,eu-central-1 node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run --provider aws --shell -- \"corepack pnpm check:changed\"`\n- Final post-gate rebase onto `origin/main` `b5bc752a48`, then focused sanity on pushed head: `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/tools.optional.test.ts src/plugins/tool-descriptor-cache.test.ts src/llm/providers/google-tool-config.test.ts packages/agent-core/src/validation.test.ts src/agents/tools/common.params.test.ts -t \"caches plugin tools without re-reading the validated name|descriptor cache|Google provider tool config|validateToolArguments|validateToolCall|createActionGate\" --reporter=verbose`\n- Earlier post-rebase focused sweep: `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/tools.optional.test.ts src/plugins/tool-descriptor-cache.test.ts src/llm/providers/google-tool-config.test.ts packages/agent-core/src/validation.test.ts packages/agent-core/src/agent-loop.test.ts src/agents/agent-tool-definition-adapter.test.ts src/agents/code-mode.test.ts src/gateway/mcp-http.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/approval-native-helpers.test.ts src/agents/tools/common.params.test.ts -t \"caches plugin tools without re-reading the validated name|descriptor cache|Google provider tool config|validateToolArguments|validateToolCall|EventStream failures|agent tool definition adapter|omits unreadable catalog tool names|omits unreadable loopback tool names|copies synthetic approver lists|createActionGate\" --reporter=verbose`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n- changed-file scrub for the reported plugin name and private path patterns.\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main`\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n- AWS Crabbox `check:changed` passed: provider `aws`, lease `cbx_31f039191f2f`, run `run_63cfbd3158dc`, exit 0.\n- Final focused sanity after the post-gate rebase passed: 5 files, 18 tests passed, 85 skipped.\n- Earlier broader focused sweep passed: 13 files, 35 tests passed, 258 skipped.\n- Branch-mode autoreview was clean with no accepted/actionable findings.\n- Current branch diff and PR body scrub pass for the reported plugin name and private paths.\n\nObserved result after fix:\n\n- Synthetic `fuzzplugin`/`mockplugin` fixtures with unreadable names, schemas, descriptions, approval fields, provider metadata, MCP catalog fields, and cached runtime descriptors no longer crash the relevant projection/resolution paths.\n- Healthy siblings, such as `mockplugin_status`, continue through materialization, descriptor caching, provider payload conversion, MCP/Gateway listing, and agent-core validation while malformed siblings are omitted or diagnosed.\n- Google/Vertex payloads omit `toolConfig` when all candidate tools are quarantined after provider projection.\n- Plugin runtime descriptor caching no longer re-reads a factory-returned tool name after validation.\n\nWhat was not tested:\n\n- Blacksmith Testbox `pnpm check:changed` was not run because `blacksmith` is not authenticated in this shell.\n- The full AWS Crabbox changed gate passed before the final clean rebase onto `b5bc752a48`; after that rebase, focused sanity, diff-check, scrub, and branch autoreview were rerun instead of chasing another moving-main full gate.\n- GitHub CI for the newest force-push is still running/pending.\n- No live third-party plugin was referenced or exercised; tests intentionally use synthetic `fuzzplugin`/`mockplugin` fixtures.\n\n## Current review state\n\n- PR remains draft while this fuzzing/hardening lane continues.\n- Latest pushed commit: `52e0654e9c38b2a5b